reviewText:
Lovely stealth game.
It can be played on first or third person point of view. There is a mix of action and reasoning, with some side quests to make it more like a role playing game.
Pros:
+ The stealth and action makes a creative use of your tools/weapons, you can complete the game without killing anyone;
+ The game is from 2004, but it is still good and fun;
+ The story is full of twists and catch your attention.
Cons:
- Some challenges take time to wait the soldiers or enemies to walk to a best position on their routes or to loot 100% on each level, so it takes time;
- Only 1 dagger and a bow as weapons, but it is a stealth game, right? The guy could carry no weapon at all;
Enjoy the game.

Old but gold: the gaming industry should take this as the stealth archetype. No way to exit from a situation with sheer force: Garret is not a muscle boy and will get killed soon.

Pros:
+ excellent stealth system, balanced with combat: you are almost forced to stay out of fights as long as you can, and are rewarded for what you get, not for who you kill;
+ maps are small but it's easy to get lost. No map indicators, only static drafts: I love this game for the courage in forcing the player to play in a conscious way;
+plenty of freedom in planning your path.

Cons:
- the graphics has not aged well: the game is only available in 4:3 resolutions and will flicker whenever the menu is opened. So poor performance;
- since there is no map indicator, it's easy to get lost and get stuck with the mission. So far I was fine without googling, but I don't know if I will keep it up like this;
- kind of awkward commands: sometimes you need to be in certain positions in order to get on a ledge or box, that exact position. Engine limits, I guess.

All in all, an awesome stealth game - the CORE of stealth games.

